    "title" => "Transportation and Land Use Planning", 
    "description" => "Examination of the interactions between transportation and land use systems; historical perspectives on transportation; characteristics of travel and demand estimation; evaluation of system performance; location theory; models of transportation and urban structure; empirical evidence of transportation-land use impacts; case study examinations. Also listed as City and Regional Planning C213." 
  }, 
  { 
    "name" => "CIV ENG.C291F", 
    "number" => 291, 
