  }, 
  { 
    "name" => "COG SCI.C127", 
    "number" => 127, 
    "units" => 3, 
    "title" => "Cognitive Neuroscience", 
    "description" => "This course will examine research investigating the neurological basis of cognition. Material covered will include the study of brain-injured patients, neurophysiological research in animals, and the study of normal cognitive processes in humans with non-invasive behavioral and physiological techniques such as functional Magnetic Resonance Imaging (fMRI), electroencephalography (EEG), and transcranial magnetic stimulation (TMS). Topics to be covered include perception, attention, memory, language, motor control, executive control, and emotion. Also listed as Psychology C127." 
  }, 
