    "units" => 3, 
    "title" => "Engineering Leadership I", 
    "description" => "Designed for professionally-oriented engineering graduate students, this course explores key management and leadership concepts relevant to technology-dependent enterprises. Topics include opportunity recognition, strategies for effective R and D, marketing innovation, disruption, cognitive inertia, product management, market selection, standards wars, two-sided markets, attracting stakeholders, business models, pricing strategies." 
