    "number" => 272, 
    "units" => 3, 
    "title" => "Engineering Leadership II", 
    "description" => "Designed for professionally-oriented engineering graduate level students, this course explores key operational, leadership, and financial concepts relevant to technology-dependent enterprises. Topics include methods to go to market, direct and indirect sales, logistics, talent management, managing creativity, project management, leadership styles, CFO-style interpretation of financial statements, funding sources, budgeting, and valuation methods." 
