    "number" => 138, 
    "units" => 3, 
    "title" => "Modern Atomic Physics", 
    "description" => "This course covers atomic, molecular, and optical physics as a quantitative description of atoms and fields, a generalized toolbox for controlling quantum systems, and a vibrant research area. Topics covered include atomic structure and spectra, atom-field interactions, topics in quantum electrodynamics, methods of resonant manipulation of quantum systems, resonance optics, and experimental techniques." 
  }, 
  { 
