  { 
    "name" => "POL SCI.110B", 
    "number" => 110, 
    "units" => 2, 
    "title" => "Cal-in-Sacramento", 
    "description" => "The purpose of this course is to provide Cal-in-Sacramento interns and other interested UC Berkeley students with a rudimentary understanding of our state government. We will focus on the state legislature and executive branch, exploring both the policy-making process and the politics in Sacramento, which we will learn are quite closely related to one another." 
