    "number" => 260, 
    "units" => 4, 
    "title" => "Public Leadership and Management", 
    "description" => "This course is designed to help students develop their skills for leading and managing groups, government agencies, nonprofit organizations, and public advocacy, with the goal of achieving positive social change. Materials include case studies, analyses, and works from several disciplines. Course is open to first and second year MPP students, but recommended for first year." 
